PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FThe health secretary committed to
OL,8,Freforming the Mental Capacity Act
OL,9,Fafter ITV News highlighted multiple
OL,10,Fcases of vulnerable adults not getting
OL,11,Fassessments, ITV News' Political
OL,12,FCorrespondent Romilly Weeks' reports,
OL,13,Fproduced by Senior Political Producer
OL,14,FElisa Menendez
OL,16,FWhen Sally Agarwal's ex-partner
OL,17,Fsuffered a catastrophic brain injury,
OL,18,Fleaving him with a five-minute memory,
OL,19,Fshe thought the system would step in
OL,20,Fand help.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FBut four years on, and amid her own
OL,8,Fcancer diagnosis, she is still
OL,9,Fproviding round-the-clock care at her
OL,10,Fhome for Mark, who is unaware that he
OL,11,Fhas been injured.
OL,13,FThe mother-of-three believes if he'd
OL,14,Fhave been given a mental capacity
OL,15,Fassessment - which judges whether a
OL,16,Fperson is capable of making decisions
OL,17,Fsafely for themselves - Mark would
OL,18,Fhave received the help they both
OL,19,Fdesperately need.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"I hoped that our systems to protect
OL,8,Fthe most vulnerable people in our
OL,9,Fsociety would work," Sally told ITV
OL,10,FNews.
OL,12,F"What I've seen - and heard about in
OL,13,Fother cases - actually is that far
OL,14,Ffrom working to protect the person,
OL,15,Fthey seem to be used to ignore the
OL,16,Fperson, to make them kind of
OL,17,Fdisappear."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FSally is one of many people ITV News
OL,8,Fhas spoken to over the past year who
OL,9,Fhave highlighted the ways the Mental
OL,10,FCapacity Act is failing their
OL,11,Fvulnerable loved ones.
OL,13,FIt comes after the tireless
OL,14,Fcampaigning of Fiona Laskaris, whose
OL,15,Fautistic son Christopher was murdered
OL,16,Fin his own home after authorities
OL,17,Ffailed to give him a mental capacity
OL,18,Fassessment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FTheir speaking out has prompted Health
OL,8,FSecretary Wes Streeting to today give
OL,9,Fhis strongest backing yet that the
OL,10,Fgovernment will reform the Act.
OL,12,FHealth Secretary Wes Streeting told
OL,13,FITV News' Romilly Weeks he is
OL,14,Fcommitted to reforming the Mental
OL,15,FCapacity Act
OL,17,FStreeting told ITV News: "It is a
OL,18,Freally serious situation because too
OL,19,Foften we've seen - and you have been
OL,20,Fshowing us - people are experiencing
OL,21,Finjury.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"The extent of harm isn't fully known,
OL,8,Fit's not assessed at the time, and
OL,9,Ftherefore people aren't receiving the
OL,10,Fhelp that they're entitled to - the
OL,11,Fsupport that they need. And they're
OL,12,Fnot being treated with the dignity and
OL,13,Fthe respect that they're owed too.
OL,15,F"So we are looking at this actively,
OL,16,Fwe're determined to take action. That
OL,17,Fwill include a review of, and
OL,18,Fultimately reform of, the Mental
OL,19,FCapacity Act."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FIn January 2022, Mark suffered a
OL,8,Fserious seizure while staying at Sally
OL,9,Fand her husband Alan's home in
OL,10,FTorquay, Devon. Their lives changed
OL,11,Fovernight, with Sally and Alan
OL,12,Fbecoming full-time carers for Mark.
OL,14,FOne night, Sally heard banging coming
OL,15,Ffrom Mark's room and went in to find
OL,16,Fhim lying on his bed where he "looked
OL,17,Fquite dead". Alan performed CPR on
OL,18,FMark as they waited for an ambulance
OL,19,Fto arrive, which took him to intensive
OL,20,Fcare.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FThere, he remained intubated for the
OL,8,Fmajority of his six-week stay, before
OL,9,Fbeing discharged from the hospital to
OL,10,Ftheir home nearby.
OL,12,FThe injury left Mark with a severe
OL,13,Fmemory impairment and as a result he
OL,14,Fnow needs help remembering to eat, to
OL,15,Ftake his life-saving medication, and
OL,16,Fround-the-clock care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"His memory from before the incident
OL,8,Fin 2022 is pretty much intact but
OL,9,Fsince then, he can only retain about
OL,10,Ffive to 10 minutes worth of memory and
OL,11,Fthen it's gone," Sally said.
OL,13,F"So that means he can't remember to do
OL,14,Fan awful lot of the things that we
OL,15,Ftake for granted. He can't remember
OL,16,Fwhat date it is, he can't remember to
OL,17,Ftake his medications."
OL,19,FEvery time Sally tells him of his
OL,20,Finjury, it is as though he is hearing
OL,21,Fit for the first time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"It's a horrible shock every time,"
OL,8,Fshe added, "he can't remember that he
OL,9,Fcan't remember."
OL,11,FWhen Mark was discharged from hospital
OL,12,Fto their home, Sally assumed "the
OL,13,Fsystem would kick in" and that he
OL,14,Fwould be supported to return to his
OL,15,Fhome in Camden, London.
OL,17,FBut no mental capacity assessment was
OL,18,Foffered to Mark, meaning he never
OL,19,Freceived the support and care he - and
OL,20,FSally's family - desperately need.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FSally recalled: "Mark had said on the
OL,8,Fphone to a social worker from his home
OL,9,Fauthority that he didn't need any
OL,10,Fcare, he didn't require any services,
OL,11,Fand so the case was closed by his home
OL,12,Fauthority... Because he doesn't know
OL,13,Fhe has a brain injury."
OL,15,FIf Mark had returned home without any
OL,16,Fhelp, he'd be in danger of further
OL,17,Fbrain injury or death, says Sally.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"Because he's so vulnerable, he could
OL,8,Fhave been exploited by other people,
OL,9,Fhe could have been made homeless and I
OL,10,Fcould not just dump him.
OL,12,F"My husband and I both agreed that we
OL,13,Fjust can't do that. We wouldn't even
OL,14,Fdo it to a dog."
OL,16,FThings worsened when Sally was
OL,17,Fdiagnosed with cancer in 2023. But she
OL,18,Fhad no time to recuperate. The night
OL,19,Fshe got home from hospital, Mark
OL,20,Fsuffered another serious seizure.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"There was no formal care in place for
OL,8,FMark, even though it was requested by
OL,9,Fclinicians. Nothing was done," Sally
OL,10,Fsays.
OL,12,FSally - who was later diagnosed with
OL,13,FPTSD - fears if she isn't there for
OL,14,FMark, that he will have no one,
OL,15,Fadding: "If I break, the whole thing
OL,16,Fbreaks."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FHow close has she been to breaking?
OL,8,F"Pretty close," she says. "I had to
OL,9,Fpretend that I didn't have cancer.
OL,10,FIt's quite a hard thing to do,
OL,11,Factually."
OL,13,FIf an assessment to judge whether Mark
OL,14,Fis capable of making decisions about
OL,15,Fhis own safety was carried out, Sally
OL,16,Fbelieves everything would have
OL,17,Funfolded differently.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"It would have made a massive
OL,8,Fdifference if I'd have been able to
OL,9,Funderstand that he needed a (mental
OL,10,Fcapacity) assessment and then ask for
OL,11,Fit," she says.
OL,13,F"The original problem - which was Mark
OL,14,Fsaying, 'I don't need any help', and
OL,15,Fthat being taken at face value -
OL,16,Fcouldn't have happened.
OL,18,F"The assessment would have found that
OL,19,Fhe didn't have capacity. And so that
OL,20,Fcould never have been used as a reason
OL,21,Ffor closing his case."
OL,26,@qD@]pmrD@Ipn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FIn October 2025, Camden Council
OL,8,Ffinally offered a package of care but
OL,9,FMark's GP has deemed it clinically
OL,10,Funsafe and it was conducted without a
OL,11,Fcapacity assessment.
OL,13,FSally is now going to court to attempt
OL,14,Fto get Camden to deliver the support
OL,15,Fher family needs. While she waits for
OL,16,Fthat judgement, her life remains on
OL,17,Fhold.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"It has been tough. But I really hope
OL,8,Fthat the law gets changed so that
OL,9,Fother people don't have to do this in
OL,10,Fthe future.
OL,12,F"It's such a terrible waste of
OL,13,Fpeople's lives and actually in the
OL,14,Fend, government resources, because
OL,15,Fdenying these people what they need is
OL,16,Fnot saving money, it's just creating
OL,17,Fbigger problems further down the line."
OL,19,FWhat has Camden Council said?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FA Camden Council spokesperson said:
OL,8,F"In Camden we always aim to work
OL,9,Fclosely with both people who require
OL,10,Fsocial care, and their families. We
OL,11,Fare confident that suitable support
OL,12,Fhas been regularly offered to meet Mr
OL,13,FManning's needs at the appropriate
OL,14,Ftime, however, we are of course ready
OL,15,Fto help with any concerns around this
OL,16,Fand to discuss this support.
OL,26,@pD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F"We do not believe that the Mental
OL,8,FCapacity Act has been a barrier in
OL,9,Fthis instance, but Camden Council is
OL,10,Fhere to engage with the government's
OL,11,Freview of the Act to ensure this works
OL,12,Fbest for our residents."
OL,14,FWhat is the Mental Capacity Act and
OL,15,Fhow could the law change?
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,FThe Mental Capacity Act was introduced
OL,8,Fin 2005 in a bid to minimise the
OL,9,Fnumber of vulnerable adults being
OL,10,Fdetained unreasonably and
OL,11,Findefinitely, and to give them more
OL,12,Fautonomy over their own care.
OL,14,FIt states that as a starting point,
OL,15,Feveryone should be presumed to have
OL,16,Fthe capacity to make decisions about
OL,17,Ftheir own safety and wellbeing, and
OL,18,Fthat an assessment should be carried
OL,19,Fout if their capacity is in doubt.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30421
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1774472757
OL,3,CThe plight of a woman caring for her
OL,4,Cex who's not aware he has a brain
OL,5,Cinjury
OL,7,F'Losing a child is the worst thing
OL,8,Fthat can happen to anyone, but I think
OL,9,Fa preventable death is the very
OL,10,Fworst,' Fiona Laskaris previously told
OL,11,FITV News in 2025, following the murder
OL,12,Fof her autistic son Christopher
OL,14,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,15,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,16,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,17,Feffectively - in particular on
OL,18,Fautistic people, adults with learning
OL,19,Fdisabilities or those with severe
OL,20,Fmental health conditions, such as
OL,21,Fbipolar and schizophrenia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/23
